  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple levels of legislation and regulation:\n\n1. International Level\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Proceeds of Crime legislation\n- Suspicious Transaction Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Components\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious financial activities\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n- Transaction monitoring and reporting\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement investigations\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture provisions\n- Criminal prosecution\n\n5. Regulated Sectors\n- Banking\n- Financial services\n- Real estate\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Casino and gambling industries\n\n6. Compliance Requirements\n- Risk assessment\n- Internal control systems\n- Staff training\n- Record-keeping\n- Regular audits\n\nThe framework aims to detect, prevent, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining financial system integrity.",
